  "prompt": "I'm a US citizen and my boyfriend is Argentinean; if we get married in the US, how long will it take for him to be qualified to work in the US?",
  "response": "The process of obtaining work authorization for a foreign spouse in the US involves several steps:\n\n1. After marriage, your husband would apply for a green card through marriage (immigrant visa):\n- File Form I-130 (Petition for Alien Relative)\n- File Form I-485 (Application to Register Permanent Residence)\n- Attend an immigration interview\n\n2. Processing times vary but generally take 10-13 months:\n- USCIS processing: 7-10 months\n- Interview and background checks: additional time\n\n3. Once the green card is approved, he can:\n- Work legally in the US\n- Apply for a work permit (Employment Authorization Document)\n- Start working immediately after receiving the green card\n\n4. Alternate option: K-1 Fianc\u00e9 Visa\n- If not yet married, he could enter US on a fianc\u00e9 visa\n- Must marry within 90 days of entry\n- Apply for work authorization after marriage\n\n5. Possible expedited options:\n- Premium processing\n- Military service members\n- Exceptional circumstances\n\nRecommendation: Consult an immigration lawyer for personalized advice specific to your situation, as processing times and requirements can change.",
